comment_data.body:
why does this care about `now != last` ? it should just always update.

    set_vim_var_nr(VV_LASTACTIVITY, (varnumber_T)os_realtime);

if we really want to avoid unnecessary operations, we could set a global,

    last_activity = os_realtime(..)

 and only update `VV_LASTACTIVITY` *when* `v:lastactivity` is actually *requested* from user code. I'm not sure if there's precedent for that, but AI could probably sketch something. It may require adding a special-case to `get_vim_var_nr`, or perhaps introducing a special function analogous to `set_vcount` (except for the "get" case: `get_vlastactivity`)

